President Biden spoke at the Long Island Railroad West Side Train Yard in New York City to announce the beginning of construction on the new Hudson Tunnel. He emphasized the importance of investing in infrastructure and improving rail transit in the country. The President highlighted the critical role that the Gateway Program, which includes the new tunnel, plays in enhancing the Northeast Corridor's speed, capacity, reliability, and safety. He also mentioned other rail projects, such as the Portal North Bridge, the East River Tunnel, and the Susquehanna Bridge, that are part of the broader effort to improve train travel in the region. President Biden emphasized that these investments will create jobs for American workers and help rebuild the country's middle class. He concluded his speech by expressing optimism about America's prospects and urging the nation to remember its capacity for achieving great things.